wfAtmLecConfigTable.name: wfAtmLecConfigTable
wfAtmLecConfigTable.description: ATM LEC Interface table - One per LEC Client This table deals with configuration and operational status

wfAtmLecConfigEntry.name: wfAtmLecConfigEntry
wfAtmLecConfigEntry.description: per LEC Client objects - wfAtmLecCct corresponds to Wellfleet circuit number

wflecConfDelete.name: wflecConfDelete
wflecConfDelete.description: Indication to create or delete an ATM LE Client Config Entry from the MIB

wflecRowStatus.name: wflecRowStatus
wflecRowStatus.description: Indication to create or delete an ATM LE Client. This will remove the LEC from the Emulated LAN. However, the instance is not removed from the MIB

wflecConfigCct.name: wflecConfigCct
wflecConfigCct.description: This corresponds to the Wellfleet circuit number

wflecOwner.name: wflecOwner
wflecOwner.description: The entity that configured this entry and is therefore using the resources assigned to it.

wflecConfigMode.name: wflecConfigMode
wflecConfigMode.description: Indicates whether this LAN Emulation Client should auto-configure the next time it is (re)started.

wflecConfigLanType.name: wflecConfigLanType
wflecConfigLanType.description: C2 - LEC LAN Type The data frame format which this client will use the next time it returns to the Initial State. Auto-configuring clients use this parameter in their Configure requests. Manually-configured clients use it in their Join requests.

wflecConfigMaxDataFrameSize.name: wflecConfigMaxDataFrameSize
wflecConfigMaxDataFrameSize.description: C3 Maximum Data Frame Size. The maximum data frame size which this client will use the next time it returns to the Initial State. Auto-configuring clients use this parameter in their Configure requests. Manually-configured clients use it in their Join requests. This MIB object will not be overwritten with the new value from a LE_{JOIN,CONFIGURE}_RESPONSE. Instead, lecActualMaxDataFrameSize will be.'

wflecConfigLanName.name: wflecConfigLanName
wflecConfigLanName.description: C5 ELAN Name. The ELAN Name this client will use the next time it returns to the Initial State. Auto-configuring clients use this parameter in their Configure requests. Manually-configured clients use it in their Join requests. This MIB object will not be overwritten with the new value from a LE_{JOIN,CONFIGURE}_RESPONSE. Instead, lecActualMaxDataFrameSize will be.'

wflecConfigLesAtmAddress.name: wflecConfigLesAtmAddress
wflecConfigLesAtmAddress.description: C9 LE Server ATM Address. The LAN Emulation Server which this client will use the next time it is started in manual configuration mode. When lecConfigMode is 'automatic', there is no need to set this address, and no advantage to doing so. The client will use the LECS to find a LES, putting the auto-configured address in lecActualLesAtmAddress while leaving lecConfigLesAtmAddress alone.

wflecControlTimeout.name: wflecControlTimeout
wflecControlTimeout.description: C7 Control Time-out. Time out period used for timing out most request/response control frame most request/response control frame interactions.

wflecMaxUnknownFrameCount.name: wflecMaxUnknownFrameCount
wflecMaxUnknownFrameCount.description: C10 Maximum Unknown Frame Count. This parameter MUST be less than or equal to 10. (See parameter C11)

wflecMaxUnknownFrameTime.name: wflecMaxUnknownFrameTime
wflecMaxUnknownFrameTime.description: C11 Maximum Unknown Frame Time. This parameter MUST be greater than or equal to 1.0 seconds. Within the period of time defined by the Maximum Unknown Frame Time, a LE Client will send no more than Maximum Unknown Frame Count frames to a given MAC address or Route Designator without also initiating the address resolution protocol to resolve that MAC address or Route Designator. This time value is expressed in seconds.

wflecVccTimeoutPeriod.name: wflecVccTimeoutPeriod
wflecVccTimeoutPeriod.description: C12 VCC Timeout Period. A LE Client may release any Data Direct or Multicast Send VCC that it has not used to transmit or receive any data frames for the length of the VCC Timeout Period. This time value is expressed in seconds.

wflecMaxRetryCount.name: wflecMaxRetryCount
wflecMaxRetryCount.description: C13 Maximum Retry Count. A LE CLient MUST not retry a LE-ARP for a given frame's LAN destination more than Maximum Retry Count times, after which it must discard the frame.

wflecAgingTime.name: wflecAgingTime
wflecAgingTime.description: C17 Aging Time. The maximum time that a LE Client will maintain an entry in its LE-ARP cache in the absence of a verification of that relationship.

wflecForwardDelayTime.name: wflecForwardDelayTime
wflecForwardDelayTime.description: C18 Forward Delay Time. The maximum time that a LE Client will maintain an entry in its LE-ARP cache in the absence of a verification of that relationship, so long as the Topology Change flag C19 is true.

wflecExpectedArpResponseTime.name: wflecExpectedArpResponseTime
wflecExpectedArpResponseTime.description: C20 Expected LE_ARP Reponse Time. The maximum time (seconds) that the LEC expects an LE_ARP_REQUEST/ LE_ARP_RESPONSE cycle to take. Used for retries and verifies.

wflecFlushTimeOut.name: wflecFlushTimeOut
wflecFlushTimeOut.description: C21 Flush Time-out. Time limit (seconds) to wait to receive a LE_FLUSH_RESPONSE after the LE_FLUSH_REQUEST has been sent before taking recovery action.

wflecPathSwitchingDelay.name: wflecPathSwitchingDelay
wflecPathSwitchingDelay.description: C22 Path Switching Delay. The time (seconds) since sending a frame to the BUS after which the LE Client may assume that the frame has been either discarded or delivered to the recipient. May be used to bypass the Flush protocol.

wflecLocalSegmentID.name: wflecLocalSegmentID
wflecLocalSegmentID.description: C23 Local Segment ID. The segment ID of the emulated LAN. This is only required for IEEE 802.5 clients that are Source Routing bridges.'

wflecMulticastSendType.name: wflecMulticastSendType
wflecMulticastSendType.description: C24 Multicast Send VCC Type. Signalling parameter that SHOULD be used by the LE Client when establishing the Multicast Send VCC. This is the method to be used by the LE Client when specifying traffic parameters when it sets up the Multicast Send VCC for this emulated LAN.

wflecMulticastSendAvgRate.name: wflecMulticastSendAvgRate
wflecMulticastSendAvgRate.description: C25 Multicast Send VCC AvgRate. Signalling parameter that SHOULD be used by the LE Client when establishing the Multicast Send VCC. Forward and Backward Sustained Cell Rate to be requested by LE Client when setting up Multicast Send VCC, if using Variable bit rate codings.

wflecMulticastSendPeakRate.name: wflecMulticastSendPeakRate
wflecMulticastSendPeakRate.description: C26 Multicast Send VCC PeakRate. Signalling parameter that SHOULD be used by the LE Client when establishing the Multicast Send VCC. Forward and Backward Peak Cell Rate to be requested by LE Client when setting up Multicast Send VCC, if using Variable bit rate codings.

wflecConnectionCompleteTimer.name: wflecConnectionCompleteTimer
wflecConnectionCompleteTimer.description: C28 Connection Complete Timer. Optional. In Connection Establishment this is the time period in which data or a READY_IND message is expected from a Calling Party.

wflecFlushEnable.name: wflecFlushEnable
wflecFlushEnable.description: Flush Protocol enable/disable - ATM_LEC_FLUSH_ENABLED - ATM LE flush protocol is used when switching VCs. If the Flush timeout (wflecFlushTimeOut) expires data for that MAC address will start flowing over the old VC again. ATM_LEC_FLUSH_DISABLED - ATM LE flush protocol is not used. Instead data for that MAC address will automatically start flowing over the new VC once the Path Switching delay timeout (wflecPathSwitchingDelay) has expired.

wflecConfigRetry.name: wflecConfigRetry
wflecConfigRetry.description: This attribute specifies how many retries should be attempted if any part of the config phase fails. The config phase starts with setting up the config direct VC and ends when a JOIN response is received. The default is 0 which means retry forever with a maximum timeout of 30 seconds between each retry. The time between each retry will start at 2 seconds and double from that point (never exceeding 30 seconds).

wflecMulticastFwdTimeout.name: wflecMulticastFwdTimeout
wflecMulticastFwdTimeout.description: The attribute specifies how many seconds to wait for the Multicast Forward VC to be set up before retrying. The retry will include closing the Multicast Send VC (if it has been opened) and reARPing for the BUS. A successful ARP response will result in the setup of the Multicast Send which in turn should result in the BUS setting up the Multicast Forward VC.

wflecMulticastFwdRetry.name: wflecMulticastFwdRetry
wflecMulticastFwdRetry.description: The attribute specifies how many retries should be made to get the Multicast Forward VC setup. The LEC will retry after wflecMulticastFwdTimeout seconds and will double this timeout for each each retry which follows. The timeout will not exeed 30 seconds however. After wflecMulticastFwdRetry retries, the LEC will restart itself. If wflecMulticastFwdRetry is set to 0 it will retry the BUS phase forever and will never restart itself.

wflecDebugLevel.name: wflecDebugLevel
wflecDebugLevel.description: Debug Levels - The level of debug desired from the Portable LEC code LEC_DBG_OFF - 0 LEC_DBG_WARN - 1 LEC_DBG_ERR - 2 LEC_DBG_MSG - 4 LEC_DBG_DBG - 8 LEC_DBG_VERBOSE - 16 This values above can be used separately, or OR'd together for a combination of debug levels. For example, to see both WARN and ERR messages, LEC_DBG_WARN OR LEC_DBG_ERR = 3, so set this object to 3.

wflecConfigLECSAtmAddress.name: wflecConfigLECSAtmAddress
wflecConfigLECSAtmAddress.description: The LE Config Server Address to be used. If left (or set) to NULL_VAL the well-known LECS ATM address will be used.

wflecConfigV2Capable.name: wflecConfigV2Capable
wflecConfigV2Capable.description: Indication to enable or disable LANE V2 support for this ATM LE Client.

wfAtmLecStatusTable.name: wfAtmLecStatusTable
wfAtmLecStatusTable.description: Lan Emulation Status Group Read-only table containing identification, status, and operational information about the LAN Emulation Clients this agent manages

wfAtmLecStatusEntry.name: wfAtmLecStatusEntry
wfAtmLecStatusEntry.description: per LEC Client objects - wfAtmLecCct corresponds to Wellfleet circuit number

wflecStatusCct.name: wflecStatusCct
wflecStatusCct.description: This corresponds to the Wellfleet circuit number

wflecID.name: wflecID
wflecID.description: C14 LE Client Identifier. Each LE Client requires a LE Client Identifier (LECID) assigned by the LE Server during the Join phase. The LECID is placed in control requests by the LE Client and MAY be used for echo suppression on multicast data frames sent by that LE Client. This value MUST NOT change without terminating the LE Client and returning to the Initial state. A valid LECID MUST be in the range X'0001' through X'FEFF'. The value of this object is only meaningful for a LEC that is connected to a LES. For a LEC which does not belong to an emulated LAN, the value of this object is defined to be 0.'

wflecInterfaceState.name: wflecInterfaceState
wflecInterfaceState.description: Indicates the state for the LE Client

wflecLastFailureRespCode.name: wflecLastFailureRespCode
wflecLastFailureRespCode.description: Failure response code. Status code from the last failed Configure response or Join response. Failed responses are those for which the LE_CONFIGURE_RESPONSE / LE_JOIN_RESPONSE frame contains a non-zero code, or fails to arrive within a timeout period. If none of this client's requests have failed, this object has the value 'none'. If the failed response contained a STATUS code that is not defined in the LAN Emulation specification, this object has the value 'undefinedError'. The value 'timeout' is self-explanatory. Other failure codes correspond to those defined in the specification, although they may have different numeric values.

wflecLastFailureState.name: wflecLastFailureState
wflecLastFailureState.description: Last failure state The state this client was in when it updated the 'lecLastFailureRespCode'. If 'lecLastFailureRespCode' is 'none', this object has the value initialState(1).

wflecProtocol.name: wflecProtocol
wflecProtocol.description: The LAN Emulation protocol which this client supports, and specifies in its LE_JOIN_REQUESTs.

wflecVersion.name: wflecVersion
wflecVersion.description: The LAN Emulation protocol version which this client supports, and specifies in its LE_JOIN_REQUESTs.

wflecTopologyChange.name: wflecTopologyChange
wflecTopologyChange.description: C19 Topology Change. Boolean indication that the LE Client is using the Forward Delay Time C18, instead of the Ageing Time C17, to age entries in its LE-ARP cache.

wflecConfigServerAtmAddress.name: wflecConfigServerAtmAddress
wflecConfigServerAtmAddress.description: The ATM address of the LECS for this Client

wflecConfigSource.name: wflecConfigSource
wflecConfigSource.description: Indicates whether this LAN Emulation Client used the LAN Emulation Configuration Server, and, if so, what method it used to establish the Configuration Direct VCC.

wflecActualLanType.name: wflecActualLanType
wflecActualLanType.description: C2 - LEC LAN Type The data frame format that this LAN Emulation Client is using right now. This may come from lecConfigLanType, the LAN Emulation Configuration Server, or the LAN Emulation Server

wflecActualMaxDataFrameSize.name: wflecActualMaxDataFrameSize
wflecActualMaxDataFrameSize.description: C3 Maximum Data Frame Size. The maximum data frame size that this LAN Emulation client is using right now. This may come from lecConfigLanType, the LAN Emulation Configuration Server, or the LAN Emulation Server

wflecActualLanName.name: wflecActualLanName
wflecActualLanName.description: C5 ELAN Name. The identity of the emulated LAN which this client last joined, or wishes to join. This may come from lecConfigLanType, the LAN Emulation Configuration Server, or the LAN Emulation Server

wflecActualLesAtmAddress.name: wflecActualLesAtmAddress
wflecActualLesAtmAddress.description: C9 LE Server ATM Address. The LAN Emulation Server address currently in use or most recently attempted. If no LAN Emulation Server attachment has been tried, this object's value is the zero-length string.'

wflecProxyClient.name: wflecProxyClient
wflecProxyClient.description: C4 Proxy When a client joins an ATM emulated LAN, it indicates whether it wants to act as a proxy. Proxy clients are allowed to represent unregistered MAC addresses, and receive copies of LE_ARP_REQUEST frames for such addresses.'

wfAtmLecOperConfigTable.name: wfAtmLecOperConfigTable
wfAtmLecOperConfigTable.description: ATM LEC Interface table - One per LEC Client This table deals with configuration and operational status

wfAtmLecOperConfigEntry.name: wfAtmLecOperConfigEntry
wfAtmLecOperConfigEntry.description: per LEC Operation Config objects - wfAtmLecOperConfigCct corresponds to Wellfleet circuit number

wflecOperConfigCct.name: wflecOperConfigCct
wflecOperConfigCct.description: This corresponds to the Wellfleet circuit number

wflecOperConfigControlTimeout.name: wflecOperConfigControlTimeout
wflecOperConfigControlTimeout.description: C7 Control Time-out. Time out period used for timing out most request/response control frame most request/response control frame interactions.

wflecOperConfigMaxUnknownFrameCount.name: wflecOperConfigMaxUnknownFrameCount
wflecOperConfigMaxUnknownFrameCount.description: C10 Maximum Unknown Frame Count. This parameter MUST be less than or equal to 10. (See parameter C11)

wflecOperConfigMaxUnknownFrameTime.name: wflecOperConfigMaxUnknownFrameTime
wflecOperConfigMaxUnknownFrameTime.description: C11 Maximum Unknown Frame Time. This parameter MUST be greater than or equal to 1.0 seconds. Within the period of time defined by the Maximum Unknown Frame Time, a LE Client will send no more than Maximum Unknown Frame Count frames to a given MAC address or Route Designator without also initiating the address resolution protocol to resolve that MAC address or Route Designator. This time value is expressed in seconds.

wflecOperConfigVccTimeoutPeriod.name: wflecOperConfigVccTimeoutPeriod
wflecOperConfigVccTimeoutPeriod.description: C12 VCC Timeout Period. A LE Client may release any Data Direct or Multicast Send VCC that it has not used to transmit or receive any data frames for the length of the VCC Timeout Period. This time value is expressed in seconds.

wflecOperConfigMaxRetryCount.name: wflecOperConfigMaxRetryCount
wflecOperConfigMaxRetryCount.description: C13 Maximum Retry Count. A LE CLient MUST not retry a LE-ARP for a given frame's LAN destination more than Maximum Retry Count times, after which it must discard the frame.

wflecOperConfigAgingTime.name: wflecOperConfigAgingTime
wflecOperConfigAgingTime.description: C17 Aging Time. The maximum time that a LE Client will maintain an entry in its LE-ARP cache in the absence of a verification of that relationship.

wflecOperConfigForwardDelayTime.name: wflecOperConfigForwardDelayTime
wflecOperConfigForwardDelayTime.description: C18 Forward Delay Time. The maximum time that a LE Client will maintain an entry in its LE-ARP cache in the absence of a verification of that relationship, so long as the Topology Change flag C19 is true.

wflecOperConfigTopologyChange.name: wflecOperConfigTopologyChange
wflecOperConfigTopologyChange.description: C19 Topology Change. Boolean indication that the LE Client is using the Forward Delay Time C18, instead of the Ageing Time C17, to age entries in its LE-ARP cache.

wflecOperConfigExpectedArpResponseTime.name: wflecOperConfigExpectedArpResponseTime
wflecOperConfigExpectedArpResponseTime.description: C20 Expected LE_ARP Reponse Time. The maximum time (seconds) that the LEC expects an LE_ARP_REQUEST/ LE_ARP_RESPONSE cycle to take. Used for retries and verifies.

wflecOperConfigFlushTimeOut.name: wflecOperConfigFlushTimeOut
wflecOperConfigFlushTimeOut.description: C21 Flush Time-out. Time limit (seconds) to wait to receive a LE_FLUSH_RESPONSE after the LE_FLUSH_REQUEST has been sent before taking recovery action.

wflecOperConfigPathSwitchingDelay.name: wflecOperConfigPathSwitchingDelay
wflecOperConfigPathSwitchingDelay.description: C22 Path Switching Delay. The time (seconds) since sending a frame to the BUS after which the LE Client may assume that the frame has been either discarded or delivered to the recipient. May be used to bypass the Flush protocol.

wflecOperConfigLocalSegmentID.name: wflecOperConfigLocalSegmentID
wflecOperConfigLocalSegmentID.description: C23 Local Segment ID. The segment ID of the emulated LAN. This is only required for IEEE 802.5 clients that are Source Routing bridges.'

wflecOperConfigMulticastSendType.name: wflecOperConfigMulticastSendType
wflecOperConfigMulticastSendType.description: C24 Multicast Send VCC Type. Signalling parameter that SHOULD be used by the LE Client when establishing the Multicast Send VCC. This is the method to be used by the LE Client when specifying traffic parameters when it sets up the Multicast Send VCC for this emulated LAN.

wflecOperConfigMulticastSendAvgRate.name: wflecOperConfigMulticastSendAvgRate
wflecOperConfigMulticastSendAvgRate.description: C25 Multicast Send VCC AvgRate. Signalling parameter that SHOULD be used by the LE Client when establishing the Multicast Send VCC. Forward and Backward Sustained Cell Rate to be requested by LE Client when setting up Multicast Send VCC, if using Variable bit rate codings.

wflecOperConfigMulticastSendPeakRate.name: wflecOperConfigMulticastSendPeakRate
wflecOperConfigMulticastSendPeakRate.description: C26 Multicast Send VCC PeakRate. Signalling parameter that SHOULD be used by the LE Client when establishing the Multicast Send VCC. Forward and Backward Peak Cell Rate to be requested by LE Client when setting up Multicast Send VCC, if using Variable bit rate codings.

wflecOperConfigConnectionCompleteTimer.name: wflecOperConfigConnectionCompleteTimer
wflecOperConfigConnectionCompleteTimer.description: C28 Connection Complete Timer. Optional. In Connection Establishment this is the time period in which data or a READY_IND message is expected from a Calling Party.

wfAtmLecStatisticsEntry.name: wfAtmLecStatisticsEntry
wfAtmLecStatisticsEntry.description: Entry contains statistics for each LEC

wflecArpRequestsOut.name: wflecArpRequestsOut
wflecArpRequestsOut.description: The number of MAC-to-ATM ARP requests made by this LAN Emulation client over the LUNI associated with this emulated packet interface.

wflecArpRequestsIn.name: wflecArpRequestsIn
wflecArpRequestsIn.description: The number of MAC-to-ATM ARP requests received by this LAN Emulation client over the LUNI associated with this emulated packet interface. Requests may arrive on the Control Direct VCC or on the Control Distribute VCC, depending upon how the LES is implemented and the chances it has had for learning. This counter covers both VCCs.

wflecArpRepliesOut.name: wflecArpRepliesOut
wflecArpRepliesOut.description: The number of MAC-to-ATM ARP replies sent by this LAN Emulation client over the LUNI associated with this emulated packet interface.

wflecArpRepliesIn.name: wflecArpRepliesIn
wflecArpRepliesIn.description: The number of MAC-to-ATM ARP replies received by this LAN Emulation client over the LUNI associated with this emulated packet interface. This count includes all such replies, whether solicited or not. Replies may arrive on the Control Direct VCC or on the Control Distribute VCC, depending upon how the LES is implemented. This counter covers both VCCs.

wflecControlFramesOut.name: wflecControlFramesOut
wflecControlFramesOut.description: The total number of control packets sent by this LAN Emulation client over the LUNI associated with this emulated packet interface.

wflecControlFramesIn.name: wflecControlFramesIn
wflecControlFramesIn.description: The total number of control packets received by this LAN Emulation client over the LUNI associated with this emulated packet interface

wflecSvcFailures.name: wflecSvcFailures
wflecSvcFailures.description: The number of SVCs which this client tried to, but failed to, open.

wflecStatisticsCct.name: wflecStatisticsCct
wflecStatisticsCct.description: This corresponds to the Wellfleet circuit number

wflecUnknownFramesDropped.name: wflecUnknownFramesDropped
wflecUnknownFramesDropped.description: The number of frames that have been dropped due to unknown frame pacing.

wfAtmLecServerVccTable.description: Lan Emulation Client - Server VCC Table

wfAtmLecServerVccEntry.name: wfAtmLecServerVccEntry
wfAtmLecServerVccEntry.description: Entry contains statistics for each LEC

wflecConfigDirectInterface.name: wflecConfigDirectInterface
wflecConfigDirectInterface.description: The interface associated with the Configuration Direct VCC. If no Configuration Direct VCC exists, this object has the value 0. Otherwise, the objects ( wflecConfigDirectInterface, wflecConfigDirectVPI, wflecConfigDirectVCI ) identify the circuit

wflecConfigDirectVpi.name: wflecConfigDirectVpi
wflecConfigDirectVpi.description: If the Configuration Direct VCC exists, this object contains the VPI which identifies that VCC at the point where it connects to this LE client. Otherwise, this object has the value 0.

wflecConfigDirectVci.name: wflecConfigDirectVci
wflecConfigDirectVci.description: If the Configuration Direct VCC exists, this object contains the VCI which identifies that VCC at the point where it connects to this LE client. Otherwise, this object has the value 0.

wflecControlDirectInterface.name: wflecControlDirectInterface
wflecControlDirectInterface.description: The interface associated with the Control Direct VCC. If no Control Direct VCC exists, this object has the value 0. Otherwise, the objects ( wflecControlDirectInterface, wflecControlDirectVPI, wflecControlDirectVCI ) identify the circuit

wflecControlDirectVpi.name: wflecControlDirectVpi
wflecControlDirectVpi.description: If the Control Direct VCC exists, this object contains the VPI which identifies that VCC at the point where it connects to this LE client. Otherwise, this object has the value 0.

wflecControlDirectVci.name: wflecControlDirectVci
wflecControlDirectVci.description: If the Control Direct VCC exists, this object contains the VCI which identifies that VCC at the point where it connects to this LE client. Otherwise, this object has the value 0.

wflecControlDistributeInterface.name: wflecControlDistributeInterface
wflecControlDistributeInterface.description: The interface associated with the Control Distribute VCC. If no Control Distribute VCC exists, this object has the value 0. Otherwise, the objects ( wflecControlDistributeInterface, wflecControlDistributeVPI, wflecControlDistributeVCI ) identify the circuit

wflecControlDistributeVpi.name: wflecControlDistributeVpi
wflecControlDistributeVpi.description: If the Control Distribute VCC exists, this object contains the VPI which identifies that VCC at the point where it connects to this LE client. Otherwise, this object has the value 0.

wflecControlDistributeVci.name: wflecControlDistributeVci
wflecControlDistributeVci.description: If the Control Distribute VCC exists, this object contains the VCI which identifies that VCC at the point where it connects to this LE client. Otherwise, this object has the value 0.

wflecMulticastSendInterface.name: wflecMulticastSendInterface
wflecMulticastSendInterface.description: The interface associated with the Multicast Send VCC. If no Multicast Send VCC exists, this object has the value 0. Otherwise, the objects ( wflecMulticastSendInterface, wflecMulticastSendVPI, wflecMulticastSendVCI ) identify the circuit

wflecMulticastSendVpi.name: wflecMulticastSendVpi
wflecMulticastSendVpi.description: If the Multicast Send VCC exists, this object contains the VPI which identifies that VCC at the point where it connects to this LE client. Otherwise, this object has the value 0.

wfAtmLecAtmAddressEntry.name: wfAtmLecAtmAddressEntry
wfAtmLecAtmAddressEntry.description: Entry contains ATM address for a LE CLient

wflecAtmAddress.name: wflecAtmAddress
wflecAtmAddress.description: The ATM address this row describes. This could be either a primary address or a secondary address.

wflecAtmAddressStatus.name: wflecAtmAddressStatus
wflecAtmAddressStatus.description: Used to create and delete rows in this table. A management station cannot disable an ATM address while the client is up

wflecAtmAddressCct.name: wflecAtmAddressCct
wflecAtmAddressCct.description: This corresponds to the Wellfleet circuit number

wfAtmLecMacAddressTable.name: wfAtmLecMacAddressTable
wfAtmLecMacAddressTable.description: LAN Emulation Client - MAC Addresses table

wfAtmLecMacAddressEntry.name: wfAtmLecMacAddressEntry
wfAtmLecMacAddressEntry.description: Entry contains MAC address for a LE CLient

wflecMacAddress.name: wflecMacAddress
wflecMacAddress.description: The MAC address this row describes. This could be either a primary address or a secondary address.

wflecMacAddressAtmBinding.name: wflecMacAddressAtmBinding
wflecMacAddressAtmBinding.description: The ATM Address registered for wflecMacAddress

wflecMacAddressCct.name: wflecMacAddressCct

wfAtmLeArpTable.name: wfAtmLeArpTable
wfAtmLeArpTable.description: Lan Emulation Client ARP Cache Group This table provides access to an ATM LAN Emulation Client's MAC-to-ATM ARP cache. It contains entries for unicast addresses and for the broadcast address, but not for multicast MAC addresses.

wfAtmLeArpEntry.name: wfAtmLeArpEntry
wfAtmLeArpEntry.description: entry of MAC address to ATM address

wfleArpMacAddress.name: wfleArpMacAddress
